      {
         "id": "SECTION_images",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Images from University Johannesburg\n\nThese images are copyright for University Johannesburg and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 1</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgShona\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgShona', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Photos of a Shona kitchen. In the top left, we see a photo of the kitchen with the door closed. In the top right, we see the back of the kitchen. In the bottom section, there are images of the interior of the structure. These photos were taken by Brian Z. Muratu (<htcite0>) and are being used under the terms defined by the University of Johannesburg, which shared the dissertation under the <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</a> license.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Mathematical Games: Hands and music - In this text, with the help of the music produced by our hands, we reinforce the understanding of counting from 0 to 10. (<htcite1>)</li><li>Physics: Cooking with numbers - Generally, recipes contain natural numbers. However, the final result is quite real. (<htcite2>)</li><li>Physics: Limiting - In this study, we establish limitations on sizes, thereby expanding the use of knowledge. (<htcite3>)</li><li>Physics: There is something else - In this text, we return to the kitchen to check how much is left of the ingredients from a recipe. (<htcite4>)</li><li>Physics: Together we are strong - In this text, we see how the four operations, when combined, open the doors to so much knowledge (<htcite5>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
